2. The boys find a conch shell that they use as a symbol of government and leadership (and respect) Throughout the book, the boys lose the meaning of the conch, it ultimately becomes powerless and they boys corrupt their government<new>The fear of the unknown and its resulting consequences <ans>When the boys were unsure if there was a beastie on the island, so they acted out of fear and joined Jack's dictatorship<new>The dangers of mob mentality <ans>1. The mock hunt with Robert 
